			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">For me then Blade Strike is my most effecient nuke at 8.94 DPM and Pyrilen Skin is 8.07 DPM (with Conservation of Xegony)
<br />

<br />
10% efficieny loss is not a bad trade imo for the unresistable nature of it (this is allowing for maximum crit effects aswell).
<br />

<br />
The best nuke mana efficiency for mages will be 9.27 DPM (Ancient DD, 20% OoW Mana pres, 45% OoW Fire focus) compared to Pyrilen Skin's 8.11 DPM or so (20% mana pres, compared to the 18% I have atm with Conservation of Xegony).
<br />

<br />
Even in this instance I wil find it very useful indeed. As soon as you start seeing resists (most raid mobs resist stuff at times) then Pryilen skin is good as it is guaranteed to do damage. Same applies in groups.
<br />

<br />
Solo then its nice to be able to pull a mob, run to pet and cast Pryilen skin before mob even reaches you. You get a 'free' 1680 damage in before the mob is even in camp effectively.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.cestusdei.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cestus Dei</a>
<br />
Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
