This hasn't been my experience... 
<br />

<br />
...but my mage is only a month old or so, so I'm still quite a n00b and could be wrong.  Last week I had a Vxed charm-tank group consisting of an L65 Cleric, L68 Enchanter, L68 Ranger, L68 Bard and myself (L65 Mage).  With a charmed pooka, aggro was maintained through buffing the charmed pet (even in combat).  However, when I foolishly debuffed/nuked/pet-killed the mob we were fighting the charmed tank immediately lost aggro.
<br />

<br />
It's possible I had numerous instances of cleric CHealing near the mob flee point (thus not being on the hate list) while the mage was buffing to get on the hate list, etc... I should probably test this in a more controlled environment.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This happens when you have more than 3 PC's on aggro at once.  4 if you include the charmed pet.  Try keeping only your cleric, chanter and ranger to snare mob on aggro and you won't have the mobs lose aggro from the charmed pet.<br />_________________<br />Magus Arthionis .68.
