<br />

<br />
I have seen this as well and timed the wear-off message -- seemed to be around 14-ish seconds.
<br />

<br />
I believe that what <span style="font-style: italic">may </span>be happening is that the "ticks" are independent of the time the spell was actually cast. If this were the case, you would expect it to last anywhere from 12+ seconds to 18- seconds, depending on where inbetween ticks you cast. The average over a lot of randomly-timed casts would be 15 seconds.
<br />

<br />
I really don't see a reason why the duration here can't be longer when there is a hit-limit on it already.
<br />

