				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Try this instead:
<br />

<br />
/pause 2, /assist tankname
<br />
/pause 2, /assist
<br />
/cast spellslotforPyrilenSkin
<br />

<br />
or
<br />

<br />
Target the incoming mob with F8 or whatever you have hotkeyed for targeting npcs. Then use the following hotkey:
<br />

<br />
/pause 2, /assist
<br />
/cast spellslotforPyrilenSkin
<br />

<br />
The pause always goes off after the command that follows on that line. I don't know why they programmed it this way.
<br />

<br />
I always target incoming mobs to do malosinia clicky on them with the T4 mask anyway, so the second hotkey set up is better for me whether on a raid situation or in a group.  The first key set up will get you the person being hit every time, if that is what you are looking for.
<br />

<br />
- Talron da Arch Magus of Bertox</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
